      "category": 2,
      "isCloned": true,
      "displayName": "Create Conditional Access policy to require MFA for admins",
      "description": "A Conditional Access policy is a rule evaluated at user login that grants or denies access to organizational resources. Conditional Access policies use signals present during login to restrict access when an expected criteria is not met. Examples of signals used to define Conditional Access policies include the user's inferred geographic location, the application being accessed by the user, and the presence or absence of a Multi-Factor Authentication response.",
      "portalLink": {
        "url": "https://entra.microsoft.com/{tenantName}/#view/Microsoft_AAD_ConditionalAccess/ConditionalAccessBlade/~/Policies/fromNav/",
        "displayName": "Microsoft Entra"
      },
      "userImpact": "First, users with administrative roles need to register for MFA. After each admin is registered, your policies then determine when they're prompted for the additional authentication factors. To view more information on your users MFA registration status please view the MFA Operational Report [Users - Microsoft 365 Lighthouse](https://lighthouse.microsoft.com/#view/Microsoft_Intune_MTM/MultiFactorAuthentication.ReactView)",
      "informationLinks": [
        {
          "url": "https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2185946",
          "displayName": "Why do I need MFA?"
        },
        {
          "url": "https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2185840",
          "displayName": "Your Password doesn't matter"
        }
